==English==
===Etymology===
From French '''[[unité]]''', from Latin '''[[unitas]]''', from adjective '''[[unus]]''', ''one'', + noun of state suffix '''[[-itas]]'''

===Pronunciation===
* [[Wiktionary:Pronunciation_key|IPA]]: /ˈjunɪti/

===Noun===
'''unity'''
# [[oneness]]; state of being one or undivided; united in mind or purpose
